modName: Beads Bikini UNP by japantarou Fixed and UNPB also BBP BBPx TBBP
summary:
6 Bikinis Standalone Craftable (Three versions of each) Includes Rockslinger's textures. With working weight slider.

Uses linen and leather strips at the Tanning rack (hide). Added BBP/TBBP versions. Added Light Armor (upgradable) options.

The original was 0 body only and a main body replacer, this mod fixes that.
descriptionHtml:
6 Bikinis Standalone Craftable. With working weight slider.

Uses Linen and leather strips at the Tanning Rack (hide).Â 

Optional updates for 1.5
Simply added a "z" to the name so it will be lowest on the list.
Light Armor (upgradable) options.

Optional ESP's are in update.

Full Bikini Light Armor 18
Bikini Top Light Armor 9
Bikini Bottom Light Armor 9

Full Bikini uses biped 32
Bikini Top uses biped 32
Bikini Bottom uses biped 45

Same biped values that Brokefoot used for his Mashup.

Want more Bikinis? [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/28099]Bikini Trouble - UNP UNPB 7B MTM DG TopModel BBP BBPx TBBP[/url] I have it setup the same as this mod.

===================================================================================================================================================

Replacers (original version) in optional.

Adds weight slider support. The original was 0 body only. This is a main body replacer.

Requires original mod installed first.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/7557]Beads Bikini UNP[/url]

I've kept it "micro" at full weight, trying to guess that's what the original author wanted.

Note:
I'm not sure if this is abandoned, but

The maker of the bead bikini hasn't even been online since the upload of that mod. The joined, and uploaded that mod all in one go and never came back.

Rockslinger who uploaded the re-text mentioned they couldn't contact them (unsurprisingly) in their info about the re-text.

I tried to contact the creator with no luck either. So I PM'd an admin on 3 Aug 2012

"Try your best to make contact to ask explicit permission but if no reply happens for a couple of weeks, I'd say go ahead and release it as you have mentioned (credit given, link back to original, etc.)

Just be aware that if the author comes back later and says you need to take it down, you will have to comply.

That is the irritating thing about using assets made by someone else and they do not include explicit permission usage and are not easy to contact."

Still no reply from mod author this many months later, so I'm uploading it.

The mod will be pulled or what ever the original mod author wants me to do.

===================================================================================================================================================
